Brazil: Amazonia (Manaus)
-------------------------
Up to the first week of July 2003, Manaus registered 2748 cases of
dengue, of which 476 were in the Zona Sul, a middle-class area but
where there is an accumulation of rubbish and industrial waste,
retaining water in which the vector mosquito is breeding.
******
Date: Tue 12 Aug 2003
From: Marilda Milagres <milagres@fclnet.com.br>
